.com%2Ftwin-mom-cant-tell-babies-apart-tips-how-to-avoid-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edressing%20us%20identically%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20giving%20us%20the%20same%20hairstyle.%20They%20thought%20it%20was%20best%20for%20us%20to%20be%20together%2C%20and%20we%20were%20supposed%20to%20ensure%20the%20other%20twin%20was%20safe.%20I%20thought%20we%20would%20grow%20up%20to%20live%20next%20door%20to%20each%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20constant%20togetherness%20was%20all%20I%20ever%20knew%20and%20was%20such%20a%20large%20part%20of%20my%20identity%20that%20when%20I%20talk%20about%20my%20childhood%2C%20I%20accidentally%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fidentical-twins-what-not-to-say-2022-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estart%20using%20the%20plural%20%26quot%3Bwe%26quot%3B%20to%20tell%20a%20story%20about%20myself%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20only%20time%20we%20were%20apart%20was%20during%20the%20short%20school%20day.%20The%20elementary%20school%20wouldn't%20let%20us%20be%20in%20the%20same%20class%20together%2C%20but%20we%20made%20sure%20to%20play%20together%20at%20recess%20and%20sit%20together%20at%20lunch.%20I%20hated%20being%20away%20from%20Rebekah.%20It%20felt%20like%20half%20of%20me%20was%20missing.%20She%20was%20my%20best%20friend%20and%20the%20person%20I%20was%20the%20most%20myself%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeing%20a%20twin%20was%20the%20most%20interesting%20thing%20about%20me.%20It%20was%20something%20that%20people%20were%20always%20curious%20about.%20Do%20we%20have%20telepathic%20powers%3F%20If%20Rebekah%20gets%20hurt%2C%20do%20I%20feel%20it%3F%20Don't%20get%20me%20wrong%2C%20I%20liked%20the%20attention%2C%20but%20no%20one%20ever%20asked%20about%20me%20specifically%20or%20wondered%20who%20I%20was%20without%20Rebekah.%20People%20wondered%20if%20we%20played%20tricks%2C%20like%20we%20were%20some%20characters%20in%20a%20Disney%20film.%20No%2C%20we%20didn't%2C%20and%20by%20high%20school%2C%20it%20was%20no%20longer%20funny%20finding%20out%20a%20boy%20meant%20to%20ask%20you%20to%20homecoming%20but%20got%20it%20wrong.%20In%20return%2C%20I%20often%20wondered%20what%20it%20was%20like%20not%20to%20be%20a%20twin.%20Was%20it%20terribly%20lonely%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22eea50a7a-8649-4de5-8eed-041b219842d8%5C%22%3EI%20compared%20myself%20to%20my%20sister%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERegardless%20of%20whether%20other%20people%20knew%20the%20difference%20between%20Rebekah%20and%20me%2C%20we%20did.%20Having%20an%20identical%20twin%20was%20an%20easy%20yardstick%20against%20which%20to%20measure%20myself.%20Her%20successes%20felt%20like%20my%20failures.%20By%20high%20school%2C%20our%20twinness%20was%20a%20competition%20of%20who%20did%20it%20better%20while%20also%20knowing%20each%20other%20so%20well%20that%20a%20sideways%20glance%20could%20cut%20like%20a%20knife.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20we%20had%20similar%20interests%20(and%20still%20do)%2C%20we%20started%20to%20find%20our%20own%20paths.%20I%20baked%20cookies%20and%20made%20a%20scrapbook%20while%20Rebekah%20wrote%20in%20her%20journal%20and%20joined%20the%20soccer%20team.%20But%20the%20most%20profound%20difference%20was%20that%20she%20knew%20what%20she%20wanted%20to%20do%20after%20high%20school%2C%20and%20I%20did%20not.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmy-identical-twins-parting-ways-college-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egoing%20to%20a%20four-year%20college%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20was%20going%20to%20get%20an%20English%20degree.%20I%20could've%20gone%20and%20done%20the%20same%2C%20but%20by%20that%20point%2C%20I%20was%20starting%20to%20see%20that%20I%20needed%20to%20be%20a%20whole%20person%20and%20not%20just%20the%20other%20half%20of%20a%20whole.%20It%20was%20the%20first%20time%20in%20my%20life%20that%20Rebekah%20wasn't%20right%20by%20my%20side.%20We%20stayed%20in%20touch%2C%20but%20we%20were%20both%20finding%20out%20what%20it%20was%20like%20to%20be%20seen%20as%20our%20own%20person%20and%20not%20the%20other%20sister's%20doppelg%C3%A4nger.%20I%20wasn't%20used%20to%20going%20places%20by%20myself%20or%20having%20to%20make%20all%20my%20own%20decisions%20without%20my%20twin's%20input.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20year%2C%20I%20ended%20up%20across%20the%20country%20at%20a%20small%20college.%20I%20met%20my%20husband%20and%20found%20out%20that%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftriplets-freak-out-when-they-realize-all-blinked-same-time-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebest%20friend%20was%20a%20triplet%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20decidedly%20cooler%20than%20a%20twin.%20He%20knew%20firsthand%20how%20incredibly%20different%20identicals%20can%20be.%20For%20the%20first%20time%2C%20being%20a%20twin%20didn't%20seem%20all%20that%20interesting.%20I%20didn't%20have%20to%20try%20to%20explain%20what%20it%20was%20like%20or%20answer%20silly%20questions.%20He%20truly%20wanted%20to%20know%20%3Cem%3Eme%3C%2Fem%3E%20as%20me.%20I%20was%20finally%20known%20and%20loved%20for%20who%20I%20was%20and%20not%20seen%20as%20part%20of%20a%20box%20set.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%20I%20think%20about%20how%20sad%2010-year-old%20me%20would%20be%20that%20Rebekah%20and%20I%20don't%20live%20next%20door%20to%20each%20other.%20But%20once%20she%20got%20over%20the%20shock%20of%20it%2C%20she'd%20be%20proud%20of%20the%20life%20I%20created%20all%20on%20my%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbeing-an-identical-twin-shaped-my-identity-in-childhood-2025-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1749934741000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68190a9aa466d2b74ab50e48%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbeing-an-identical-twin-shaped-my-identity-in-childhood-2025-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22My%20sister%20and%20I%20lived%20in%20a%20small%20town%20in%20Iowa%20in%20the%2080s%20and%20our%20most%20inter