ypical%2C%20and%20with%20that%20came%20a%20heavier%20burden%20on%20housework%20and%20childcare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20mothers%20continued%20to%20serve%20as%20the%20main%20caregivers%20even%20while%20working%20themselves%2C%20some%20men%20began%20%26quot%3Bhelping%26quot%3B%20mothers%2C%20as%20reported%20in%20a%202009%20report%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncfr.org%2Fncfr-report%2Ffocus%2Ffatherhood%2Fmythologizing-fatherhood%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENational%20Council%20on%20Family%20Relations%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBy%20the%201970s%2C%20some%20fathers%20began%20being%20more%20involved%20in%20their%20children's%20childcare.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224930%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%221970s%20dad%20changing%20diapers%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F684c3290f748d8c055f3a5c3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223698%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20feminist%20movement%20pushed%20men%20to%20take%20a%20bigger%20role%20in%20housework%20and%20childcare.%3Cp%3EClassicStock%2FClassicStock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EA%20new%20type%20of%20fatherhood%20began%20to%20emerge%20in%20the%201970s%20as%20men%20took%20on%20more%20of%20a%20nurturing%20role%20in%20their%20children's%20upbringing.%20This%20new%20archetype%2C%20named%20%26quot%3Bthe%20new%20nurturant%20father%26quot%3B%20at%20the%20time%2C%20as%20noted%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.human.cornell.edu%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FPAM%2FParenting%2FResearch-Briefs%2FUS-Fatherhood-Trends_Research-Brief.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECornell%20University%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20was%20used%20to%20describe%20fathers%20who%2C%20although%20still%20serving%20as%20the%20main%20breadwinner%20of%20the%20house%2C%20also%20took%20on%20an%20active%20role%20in%20the%20emotional%20development%20of%20their%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20this%20came%20as%20a%20response%20to%20a%20rise%20in%20absent%20fathers%20after%20no-fault%20divorce%20began%20being%20legalized%20by%201969%2C%20which%20drew%20much%20criticism%20from%20the%20growing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.andreadoucet.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F07%2FDoucet-Lee.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efeminist%20movement%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20well%20as%20scrutiny%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1080%2F15240650801935156%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epsychological%3C%2Fa%3E%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20time%20of%20shifting%20attitudes%20toward%20parenting%2C%20as%20feminists%20highlighted%20the%20invisible%20labor%20traditionally%20done%20by%20mothers%2C%20and%20as%20fathering%20researchers%20studied%20the%20effects%20of%20emotional%20detachment%20from%20absent%20fathers%20on%20both%20the%20children%20and%20the%20fathers%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20movement%20for%20%26quot%3Bnew%20fatherhood%26quot%3B%20began%20emerging%20in%20the%201980s%20as%20fathers%20continued%20to%20become%20more%20involved%20in%20their%20children's%20lives%2C%20as%20reported%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.psychologytoday.com%2Fus%2Fblog%2Fpsychology-yesterday%2F202406%2Fthe-new-and-improved-dad%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPsychology%20Today%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EAt%20the%20turn%20of%20the%2020th%20century%2C%20more%20dads%20were%20staying%20home%20with%20their%20kids.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225213%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22dad%20with%20baby%20at%20park%2C%201980s%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F684c25c63d5881a51c1b5d10%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223480%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAs%20women%20entered%20the%20workforce%2C%20men%20began%20taking%20a%20bigger%20role%20in%20child%20rearing.%3Cp%3EBarbara%20Alper%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBetween%202003%20and%202006%2C%20the%20rate%20of%20stay-at-home%20dads%20increased%20by%2050%25%2C%20as%20reported%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.apa.org%2Fpi%2Ffamilies%2Fresources%2Fchanging-father%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerican%20Psychological%20Association%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20aligned%20with%20the%20rise%20in%20women's%20wages%2C%20along%20with%20a%20growing%20sentiment%20of%20not%20wanting%20someone%20else%20to%20raise%20their%20children%2C%20per%20APA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20their%20growing%20presence%20in%20childcare%2C%20stay-at-home%20dads%20also%20reported%20feeling%20isolated%20from%20other%20stay-at-home%20parents%2C%20who%20were%20predominantly%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20trend%20continued%20after%20the%202008%20economic%20crash.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224256%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%222009%20stay%20at%20home%20dad%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F684c27e585e81483682c0b36%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222832%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERates%20of%20stay-at-home%20dads%20are%20consistent%20with%20rises%20in%20unemployment%20rates.%3Cp%3EJoe%20Amon%2FDenver%20Post%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20rates%20of%20stay-at-home%20dads%20have%20fluctuated%20over%20the%20past%2050%20years%2C%20they%20have%20consistently%20increased%20during%20periods%20of%20high%20unemployment%2C%20per%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2023%2F08%2F03%2Falmost-1-in-5-stay-at-home-parents-in-the-us-are-dads%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPew%20Research%20Center%3C%2Fa%3E.%20After%20the%202008%20financial%20crisis%2C%20many%20men%20stayed%20at%20home%20and%20provided%20childcare%20for%20their%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20Great%20Recession%2C%20we%20saw%20the%20share%20of%20all%20stay-at-home%20parents%20go%20up%20by%20several%20percentage%20points%20to%20about%2029%25%2C%26quot%3B%20Pew%20Researc